                 <table align="center" class="STAR_FUND" style="width: 875px;">
                  <tbody>
                   <tr>
                    <td style="text-align: left; vertical-align: top;">
                     <h1 src="/portals/0/images/Texas_rainstorm_color.jpg">
                      <img alt="" src="/portals/0/images/Texas_rainstorm_color.jpg" style="float: right; margin-left: 6px;"/>
                      The State of Texas Agriculture Relief Fund
                     </h1>
                     <p style="font-size: 14px; color: #244061;">
                      Many of our fellow Texans are in need of a helping hand. Texas Agriculture Farmers, Rancher, producers and agribusiness owners are rebuilding and working towards picking up the pieces after all of these natural disasters. As natural disasters continue to impact Texas farmers and ranchers, the need for donations continues.
                      <br/>
                      <br/>
                      The STAR Fund (State of Texas Agriculture Relief Fund) was created solely with monetary donations from private individuals and companies. STAR Fund money may be used to assist farmers and ranchers in rebuilding fences, restoring operations and paying for other agricultural disaster relief.
                      <br/>
                      <a href="/Home/ProductionAgriculture/DisasterAssistance/STARFund.aspx">
                       <br/>
                       Learn more about the STAR FUND here.
                      </a>
                     </p>
                    </td>
                   </tr>

                 </table>

           <div class="DnnModule DnnModule-DNN_HTML DnnModule-4660">
            <a name="4660">
            </a>
            <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="p_wrapper" width="100%">
             <tr>
              <td align="left">
               <span class="p_title" id="dnn_ctr4660_dnnTITLE_titleLabel">
                Welcome to the Texas Department of Agriculture
               </span>
              </td>
             </tr>
             <tr>
              <td align="left" valign="top">
               <div class="actionshold">
               </div>
               <div class="pcon_pos" id="dnn_ctr4660_ContentPane">
                <!-- Start_Module_4660 -->
                <div class="DNNModuleContent ModDNNHTMLC" id="dnn_ctr4660_ModuleContent">
                 <div class="Normal" id="dnn_ctr4660_HtmlModule_lblContent">
                  <table align="left" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="5" style="width: 100%; background-color: #ddd9c3;">
                   <thead>
                   </thead>
                   <tbody>
                    <tr>
                     <td style="text-align: left; vertical-align: top;">
                      <img alt="" src="/portals/0/images/Casual_Headshot_rotatedwbkgd.png" style="vertical-align: top;"/>
                     </td>
                     <td style="text-align: left; vertical-align: top;">
                      <p class="NoParagraphStyle" style="text-align: justify;">
                       Howdy Neighbors!
                       <br/>
                       <br/>
                       You may not know it, but the Texas Department of Agriculture (TDA) touches your life almost every day.  From the gas pump you used to fill up your car this morning to the salsa you’re eating at dinner, TDA was there to help. From the healthy lunches at your child’s school to the scales used to weigh your luggage at the airport, TDA was there, too.  From our role as the state consumer protection agency to administering school lunches and marketing Texas products, the TDA is a diverse and busy place.  We work hard every day to serve you.
                      </p>
                      <p class="NoParagraphStyle" style="text-align: justify;">
                       Since I was sworn into office in 2015, I’ve also worked diligently to make this agency better.  Please take some time to browse our website and learn about the many ways we’re working better, faster and more efficiently for you. As always, it is my honor to serve as your Texas Agriculture Commissioner and remind you that
                       <em>
                        Texas Agriculture Matters
                       </em>
                       !
                      </p>
                      <p class="NoParagraphStyle" style="text-align: justify;">
                       Your Servant,
                      </p>
                      <p class="NoParagraphStyle" style="text-align: justify;">
                       <img alt="Sid Miller signature" src="/portals/0/images/Sid-Miller-Blue.png"/>
                      </p>
                      <p class="NoParagraphStyle" style="text-align: justify;">
                       Sid Miller
                      </p>
                      <p>
                       Texas Agriculture Commissioner
                      </p>
                     </td>
                    </tr>
                   </tbody>
                  </table>
                 </div>
                </div>
                <!-- End_Module_4660 -->

              </td>
             </tr>

                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                       <td>
                        <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="ItemTable">
                         <tr>
                          <td align="left" class="Title" valign="top">
                           <a class="Head" href="http://www.texasagriculture.gov/NewsEvents/NewsEventsDetails/tabid/76/Article/4471/Texas-Agriculture-Memorial-Day-Honors-Those-Who-Lost-Their-Lives-in-Agriculture.aspx" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_articleLink_7">
                            <span id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblArticleName_7">
                             Texas Agriculture Memorial Day Honors Those Who Lost Their Lives in Agriculture Community in 2017
                            </span>
                           </a>
                          </td>
                         </tr>
                         <tr>
                          <td align="left" class="Summary" valign="top">
                           <span class="SubHead" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblPublishDate_7">
                            Tuesday, November 21, 2017,
                           </span>
                           <span class="Normal" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblArticleSummary_7">
                            In a solemn ceremony at the State Capitol, Texas Agriculture Commissioner Sid Miller was joined by his fellow members of the agriculture community as they honored those men and women who lost their life in the ag industry over the last year.  The 2nd Annual Texas Agriculture Memorial Day remembers those Texas farmers and ranchers who died in the previous year as a way of focusing public attention on the importance of Texas agriculture.
                           </span>
                          </td>
                         </tr>
                        </table>
                       </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                       <td>
                        <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="ItemTable">
                         <tr>
                          <td align="left" class="Title" valign="top">
                           <a class="Head" href="http://www.texasagriculture.gov/NewsEvents/NewsEventsDetails/tabid/76/Article/4460/Texas-Agriculture-Memorial-Day-Nov-21-Honors-Those-Who-Gave-so-Much-to-Agricult.aspx" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_articleLink_8">
                            <span id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblArticleName_8">
                             Texas Agriculture Memorial Day (Nov. 21) Honors Those Who Gave so Much to Agriculture Community
                            </span>
                           </a>
                          </td>
                         </tr>
                         <tr>
                          <td align="left" class="Summary" valign="top">
                           <span class="SubHead" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblPublishDate_8">
                            Thursday, November 16, 2017,
                           </span>
                           <span class="Normal" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblArticleSummary_8">
                            On Tuesday, November 21, the Texas Department of Agriculture will host the 2nd Annual Texas Agriculture Memorial Day at the Texas Capitol in Austin.  Texas Agriculture Memorial Day is a day to remember the lives and honor the sacrifices of Texas farmers and ranchers who contribute so much to our heritage and our economy.
                           </span>
                          </td>
                         </tr>
                        </table>
                       </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                       <td>
                        <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="ItemTable">
                         <tr>
                          <td align="left" class="Title" valign="top">
                           <a class="Head" href="http://www.texasagriculture.gov/NewsEvents/NewsEventsDetails/tabid/76/Article/4473/Agriculture-Commissioner-Sid-Miller-Honors-Texas-Farm-and-Ranch-Families-at-42n.aspx" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_articleLink_9">
                            <span id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblArticleName_9">
                             Agriculture Commissioner Sid Miller Honors Texas Farm and Ranch Families at 42nd Annual Family Land Heritage Ceremony
                            </span>
                           </a>
                          </td>
                         </tr>
                         <tr>
                          <td align="left" class="Summary" valign="top">
                           <span class="SubHead" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblPublishDate_9">
                            Tuesday, November 07, 2017,
                           </span>
                           <span class="Normal" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblArticleSummary_9">
                            In a celebration of agriculture and family heritage, Agriculture Commissioner Sid Miller and the Texas Department of Agriculture (TDA) honored 64 farms and ranches spanning 51 Texas counties at the 42nd Annual Family Land Heritage (FLH) ceremony at the Texas State Capitol today.
                           </span>
                          </td>
                         </tr>
                        </table>
                       </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                       <td>
                        <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="ItemTable">
                         <tr>
                          <td align="left" class="Title" valign="top">
                           <a class="Head" href="http://www.texasagriculture.gov/NewsEvents/NewsEventsDetails/tabid/76/Article/4409/Commissioner-Miller-Honors-Student-Art-Contest-Winners.aspx" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_articleLink_10">
                            <span id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblArticleName_10">
                             Commissioner Miller Honors Student Art Contest Winners
                            </span>
                           </a>
                          </td>
                         </tr>
                         <tr>
                          <td align="left" class="Summary" valign="top">
                           <span class="SubHead" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblPublishDate_10">
                            Wednesday, October 11, 2017,
                           </span>
                           <span class="Normal" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblArticleSummary_10">
                            Agriculture Commissioner Sid Miller today congratulated Emilia Davila of Laredo and Marianeé Canales of Kingsville as winners in the Texas Department of Agriculture’s (TDA) You Art What You Eat! statewide student art contest.
                           </span>
                          </td>
                         </tr>
                        </table>
                       </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                       <td>
                        <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="ItemTable">
                         <tr>
                          <td align="left" class="Title" valign="top">
                           <a class="Head" href="http://www.texasagriculture.gov/NewsEvents/NewsEventsDetails/tabid/76/Article/4403/Commissioner-Miller-Kicks-Off-National-School-Lunch-Week.aspx" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_articleLink_11">
                            <span id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblArticleName_11">
                             Commissioner Miller Kicks Off National School Lunch Week
                            </span>
                           </a>
                          </td>
                         </tr>
                         <tr>
                          <td align="left" class="Summary" valign="top">
                           <span class="SubHead" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblPublishDate_11">
                            Monday, October 09, 2017,
                           </span>
                           <span class="Normal" id="dnn_ctr498_ViewAllNews_ArticleList_lblArticleSummary_11">
                            Commissioner Miller today announced the start of National School Lunch Week, which runs Oct. 9 to 13, and emphasizes the value of leading healthy lifestyles to Texas students. In partnership with the Texas Department of Agriculture (TDA), every school day, Texas schools serve approximately 3 million healthy meals through the National School Lunch Program.
                           </span>
                          </td>
                         </tr>
                        </table>
                       </td>
                      </tr>
                     </table>
